SIMPLE: immortality
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Immortality
<hw>Im`mor*tal"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Immortalities</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L.
<ets>immortalitas</ets>: cf. F. <ets>immortalit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality or state of being immortal; exemption from
death and annihilation; unending existence; <as>as, the
<ex>immortality</ex> of the soul</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This mortal must put on <qex>immortality</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>1
Cor. xv. 53.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Exemption from oblivion; perpetuity; <as>as, the
<ex>immortality</ex> of fame</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Immortalization</ent>⟦br⟧
